{{short description|21st-century American Old Catholic bishop}} {{BLP primary sources|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name =Craig J. N. de Paulo | title = [[Primate (bishop)|Primate]] of the [[Old Catholic Confederation]] | image = Image Bishop Craig J. N. de Paulo.jpg | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | other = | motto = | ordination = June 23, 2007 | ordained_by = [[Robert Mikhail Moskal]] | consecration = September 14, 2013 | consecrated_by = [[Peter Paul Brennan]], [[Rodney R. Michel]], William J. Manseau | occupation = [[Bishop]] | alma_mater = [[Pontifical Gregorian University]] | nationality = [[United States]] | subject = | political party = | influences = | religion = [[Old Catholic Confederation]] | coat_of_arms = | signature = }}
'''Craig John Neumann de Paulo''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Old Catholic]] [[bishop]]. He is the [[Primate (bishop)|primate]] of the [[Old Catholic Confederation]] and its [[archbishop]] in the United States.
==Life and career==
De Paulo received a Ph.D. in philosophy in 1995 from the [[Pontifical Gregorian University]] in Rome.<ref>{{cite thesis|location=Rome|publisher=Pontifical Gregorian University|last=Paulo|first=Craig J. N. de|type=Ph.D.|title=Being and conversion: a phenomenological ontology of radical restlessness|year=1995|oclc=493600967}}</ref>
De Paulo was ordained as a deacon and priest in the United States in the [[Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church|Ukrainian Catholic Church]], an [[Eastern Catholic]] church within the [[Roman Catholic Church]]. In 2007, he was installed as pastor in [[East McKeesport, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{cite web|location=Carnegie, PA|publisher=Holy Trinity Ukrainian Catholic Church|website=htucc.org|title=From the 2007 family album|year=|url=http://www.htucc.org/parish_album.htm|accessdate=2014-06-11|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071102125843/http://www.htucc.org/parish_album.htm|archivedate=2007-11-02|deadurl=no}}</ref> After leaving the Roman Catholic Church, he became a bishop of the Old Catholic Confederation&nbsp;– formed in 2013&nbsp;– and became its primate and Archbishop of the United States.<ref>http://www.occus.org/primate-and-archbishop, title= Primate of the Old Catholic Confederation and Archbishop of the United States</ref>
On December 25, 2013, the [[Church of the Province of West Africa]]'s archbishop, [[Solomon Tilewa Johnson]], appointed and licensed de Paulo as his representative (styled as "[[episcopal commissary]]") for North America.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.occus.org/anglican-communion |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-05-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150328080929/http://www.occus.org/anglican-communion |archivedate=2015-03-28 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://www.cpwa.info/episcopal-commissary</ref>{{Unreliable source?|reason=WP:SELFSOURCE makes doubtful claim to represent to United Nations, see talk page|date=February 2016}}{{discuss|section=Episcopal commissary position and notability issues|date=January 2016}}
