itual reflection on the sensuality of the Byzantine Divine Liturgy|chapterurl=|editor1-last=De Paulo|editor1-first=Craig J. N.|editor2-last=Blumenthal|editor2-first=Bernhardt|editor3-last=De Paulo|editor3-first=Catherine Conroy|editor4-last=Messina|editor4-first=Patrick A|editor5-last=Rudnytzky|editor5-first=Leonid|display-editors=1|title=Confessions of love: the ambiguities of Greek Eros and Latin Caritas|series=American University Studies|volume=310|location=New York [u.a.]|publisher=Lang|isbn=9781453901717|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LDEqAQAAMAAJ|pages=209–219}}
