{{autobiography|date=March 2017}} '''Nythamar de Oliveira''' (born 22 October 1960) is a [[Brazil]]ian philosopher, theologian, and university teacher. Born in Rio de Janeiro, [[Brazil]], he is full professor at the School of Humanities of the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Rio Grande do Sul]], in [[Porto Alegre]].<ref name="NuccetelliSchutte2013">{{cite book|author1=Susana Nuccetelli|author2=Ofelia Schutte|author3=Otávio Bueno|title=A Companion to Latin American Philosophy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OyRw3gH6cTkC&pg=PT209|date=5 March 2013|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-118-61056-5|pages=156–169.}}</ref><ref name="RauscherPerez2012">{{cite book|author1=Frederick Rauscher|author2=Daniel Omar Perez|title=Kant in Brazil|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4x45GjOkEssC&pg=PA21|year=2012|publisher=University Rochester Press|isbn=978-1-58046-415-4|pages=361–}}</ref>
